                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13941053" author="rohini" created="Wed, 19 Mar 2014 21:52:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;What interprets $ to last command executed? Is it not possible to fix the source of the problem as user will also have to change the pig scripts.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13941105" author="daijy" created="Wed, 19 Mar 2014 22:48:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry, Jira eats my _ character. I mean &quot;$&amp;#95;&quot; has been interpreted. My guess is Hadoop will invoke bash, and bash does the variable substitution. Yes, if user using &quot;$&amp;#95;&quot; will find it does not work in Hadoop 2. We shall ask user to use single quote instead of double quote. I am not sure how hard it is to fix on Hadoop 2 side, but if you want, I can talk with Hadoop folks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13958110" author="daijy" created="Wed, 2 Apr 2014 20:05:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=rohini&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;rohini&quot;&gt;rohini&lt;/a&gt;, any comment on this? Would like to check this into 0.12.1 release.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13958163" author="rohini" created="Wed, 2 Apr 2014 20:55:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt; I find it failing with same error in my laptop, but on our actual clusters it succeeds. So I think hadoop2 itself is not a problem.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13958289" author="rohini" created="Wed, 2 Apr 2014 22:51:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Daniel found the cause. It was working in our clusters because 0.11 was run against hadoop 2. This error was introduced with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-3069&quot; title=&quot;Native Windows Compatibility for Pig E2E Tests and Harness&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-3069&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-3069&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; in 0.12. This patch basically reverts part of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-3069&quot; title=&quot;Native Windows Compatibility for Pig E2E Tests and Harness&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-3069&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-3069&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13958290" author="daijy" created="Wed, 2 Apr 2014 22:53:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch committed to both 0.12 branch and trunk. Thanks Rohini for review!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
